      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 181: The `adjustingAspectGeometry` guard is set and cleared synchronously around the `width`/`height` assignments. For a top-level `Window`, the window manager/compositor can clamp or confirm the size asynchronously, firing a *second* `onWidthChanged`/`onHeightChanged` after the guard has already been reset to false. That echo re-enters `applyVideoAspect()` and can cause visible jitter or leave geometry out of sync. Consider tracking the last programmatically-requested size and short-circuiting when the incoming width/height matches it, rather than relying on a purely synchronous boolean.",
